    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default color is black with an opacity (alpha) of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When lighting is calculated, shadows are created as if a ray was cast out from the light node’s position. If a sprite casts a shadow, the rays are blocked when they intersect with the sprite’s physics body. Otherwise, the sprite’s texture is used to generate a mask, and any pixel in the sprite node’s texture that has an alpha value that is nonzero blocks the light."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Shadows may be cast on content that is rendered prior to the sprite, even if that content does not otherwise interact with the light."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
